    "content_hash": "1fa1ccbc0f23d734",
    "department": "Technology",
    "description": "Purpose in Every Position\n\nPebl puts a world of talent at your fingertips. With our AI-powered Global Work Platform™, companies can hire, pay, and manage employees in 185+ countries—removing risk, red tape, and guesswork from global growth. Backed by more than a decade of compliance leadership and local expertise, Pebl helps businesses move fast, stay compliant, and scale with confidence. With Pebl, companies everywhere can hire great talent anywhere.\n\nWhere Your Work Moves the Needle.\n\nAt Pebl, every team member drives our success. Joining us means more than filling a role—you’re accountable for results and impact. Our values guide how we operate, execute, and collaborate across borders. By putting them into action, you’ll help us scale faster, compete harder, and lead the future of global work.\n\nAbout Pebl\n\nPebl is the AI-first leader in global employment. We empower companies to hire, pay, and support talent in over 185 countries without the need to set up local entities. Operating with massive momentum after our recent rebrand, we are combining our decade of deep regulatory expertise and 10+ years of proprietary data with cutting-edge AI. Our goal is to become the best AI Employer of Record (EOR) Platform in the world. As we scale, we are looking for a visionary VP of Data to build the intelligence engine that powers our growth.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe are seeking a highly technical, deeply analytical, and aggressively innovative VP/Senior Director of Data to lead our data strategy, infrastructure, and AI integration. You will not just be managing a team; you will be the chief storyteller for our data and the evangelist for our \"AI Everywhere\" initiative.\n\nBased out of our Palo Alto office, you will sit at the intersection of R\u0026D and our core business functions—specifically Marketing, Sales, Operations, Finance, and Legal—ensuring that Pebl’s vast repository of global employment and compliance data is secure, accessible, and actionable.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n1. Architect the Future (Technical \u0026 Hands-On Data Engineering)\n\n - Own the vision and execution of Pebl’s modern data infrastructure.\n\n - Serve as the ultimate technical authority on data engineering, ensuring highly scalable, performant, and reliable data pipelines.\n\n - Champion strict data security, privacy, and governance protocols to protect our global payroll, HR, and compliance data.\n\n2. Drive Actionable Business Insights (Analytical Powerhouse)\n\n - Transform complex datasets into clear, actionable strategies across all departments.\n\n - Partner with Marketing and Sales to optimize our growth funnel, CAC, and conversion rates.\n\n - Collaborate with Operations, Finance, and Legal to improve billing accuracy, payroll speed, and compliance tracking.\n\n3. Champion \"AI Everywhere\" (AI Native Operations)\n\n - Lead the charge to make Pebl a truly AI-native company.\n\n - Bring AI capabilities to our R\u0026D offerings, such as enhancing our compliance assistant, Alfie.\n\n - Engage directly with Marketing, Sales, Operations, Finance, and Legal to embed AI into their daily workflows, driving massive internal efficiency.\n\n4. Bridge the Gap (Communication \u0026 Storytelling)\n\n - Act as the ultimate translator between deep technical R\u0026D work and overarching business objectives.\n\n - Master the art of data storytelling to present complex insights to the executive team and the board in a compelling way.\n\n5. Build and Foster the Team (Leadership)\n\n - Lead the Charge: Be a hands-on, execution-oriented leader who ensures delivery of strong business results.\n\n - Be the NBA Coach: Recruit top-tier talent and assemble a high-performing team of data engineers, analysts, and AI specialists.\n\n - Be the Gardener: Foster a culture of continuous learning and psychological safety to cultivate a data-driven mindset across the entire company.\n\nWhat You Bring\n\n - Extensive Technical Background: 15+ years of experience in data engineering, data science, or analytics, with at least 5 years in a senior leadership role.\n\n - Modern Stack Mastery: Deep, hands-on expertise orchestrating our specific modern data infrastructure stack: Snowflake, Fivetran, Atlan, Looker, and Monte Carlo.\n\n - AI/ML Track Record: Proven experience deploying LLMs, machine learning models, and AI tools for both production products and internal operational workflows.\n\n - Cross-Functional Business Acumen: Demonstrated ability to collaborate with Marketing, Sales, Operations, Finance, and Legal to tie data initiatives directly to top-line growth and bottom-line efficiency.\n\n - Exceptional Communication: A track record of weaving data into compelling business narratives for non-technical stakeholders.\n\n - Work Style: Ability to work from our Palo Alto office Monday through Wednesday to collaborate directly with the executive and R\u0026D teams.\n\nOur Commitment to You\n\nAt Pebl, we’re committed to supporting our team with comprehensive rewards and benefits designed to meet diverse needs across roles and locations. Our core offerings include:\n\n - Flexible Time Off – Take the time you need to recharge.\n\n - Parental Leave – Support for growing families.\n\n - Health and Dental Insurance – Where applicable, to cover you and your loved ones.\n\n - Retirement Savings + Employee Incentive Plan – Plan for the future while sharing our success.\n\nPlease visit our career page for more information https://hellopebl.com/company/careers/.\n\nPebl is an Equal Opportunity Employer.\n\nWe power global teams and believe diverse perspectives drive innovation and impact. Employment decisions at Pebl are based on qualifications, merit, and business needs. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy, sexual orientation, or gender identity), national origin, age, disability, genetic information, veteran status, or any other status protected by applicable law. We’re committed to fostering an inclusive culture where every teammate can thrive and do the best work of their career—anywhere in the world.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
